ciscoIpStatMIB.name: ciscoIpStatMIB

revisions.description: Added the following table and objects for 64 bit packet/byte counters: cipPrecedenceXTable -> cipPrecedenceHCSwitchedPkts, cipPrecedenceHCSwitchedBytes cipMacXTable -> cipMacHCSwitchedPkts, cipMacHCSwitchedBytes
Initial version of this MIB module.

ciscoIpStatMIB.contactinfo: Cisco Systems Customer Service Postal: 170 W. Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134-1706 USA Tel: +1 800 553-NETS E-mail: ipqos-dev@cisco.com
ciscoIpStatMIB.description: Cisco IP Statistics MIB - Overview This MIB incorporates objects to provide support for the Cisco IP statistics as implemented in command interfaces ip accounting [ mac-address {input | ouput } | precedence { input | ouput } ] The above CLI provides additional IP statistics categorized by precedence of IP packets, as well as the MAC address associated with IP packets. This is a supplement to those defined in OLD-CISCO-IP-MIB.my.

PacketSource.name: PacketSource
PacketSource.description: The source of the packet the statistics is for. input statistics of the input packets. output statistics of the output packets.

cipPrecedenceTable.name: cipPrecedenceTable
cipPrecedenceTable.description: A table of entries sorted by the precedence of IP packets. The table is created and deleted via ip accounting command line interface.

cipPrecedenceEntry.name: cipPrecedenceEntry
cipPrecedenceEntry.description: An entry in the cipPrecedenceTable is created for each IP precedence value. There are 8 precedences total.

cipPrecedenceDirection.name: cipPrecedenceDirection
cipPrecedenceDirection.description: The data source for the object.

cipPrecedenceIpPrecedence.name: cipPrecedenceIpPrecedence
cipPrecedenceIpPrecedence.description: The ip precedence value this object is collected upon.

cipPrecedenceSwitchedPkts.name: cipPrecedenceSwitchedPkts
cipPrecedenceSwitchedPkts.description: Traffic, in packets, at the cipPrecedenceIpPrecedence precedence.

cipPrecedenceSwitchedBytes.name: cipPrecedenceSwitchedBytes
cipPrecedenceSwitchedBytes.description: Traffic, in bytes, at the cipPrecedenceIpPrecedence precedence.

cipMacTable.name: cipMacTable
cipMacTable.description: A table is created and deleted via ip accounting command line interface.

cipMacEntry.name: cipMacEntry
cipMacEntry.description: An entry in the cipMacTable is created for each unique MAC address which receives/sends IP packets. Entries are deleted via the command line interface.

cipMacDirection.name: cipMacDirection
cipMacDirection.description: The data source for the object.

cipMacSwitchedPkts.name: cipMacSwitchedPkts
cipMacSwitchedPkts.description: The counter in packets with respect to cipMacAddress.

cipMacSwitchedBytes.name: cipMacSwitchedBytes
cipMacSwitchedBytes.description: The counter in bytes with respect to cipMacAddress.

cipMacFreeTable.name: cipMacFreeTable
cipMacFreeTable.description: A table of free space available to store new MAC address information.

cipMacFreeEntry.name: cipMacFreeEntry
cipMacFreeEntry.description: The MAC free space table entry. Entry is created when Entries are created and deleted via ip accounting command line interface.

cipMacFreeDirection.name: cipMacFreeDirection
cipMacFreeDirection.description: The data source for the object.

cipMacFreeCount.name: cipMacFreeCount
cipMacFreeCount.description: Number of items in the MAC free space.

cipPrecedenceXTable.name: cipPrecedenceXTable
cipPrecedenceXTable.description: This table contains additional objects for the cipPrecedenceTable.

cipPrecedenceXEntry.name: cipPrecedenceXEntry
cipPrecedenceXEntry.description: An entry containing additional management information applicable to a particular precedence value.

cipPrecedenceHCSwitchedPkts.name: cipPrecedenceHCSwitchedPkts
cipPrecedenceHCSwitchedPkts.description: Traffic, in packets, at the cipPrecedenceIpPrecedence precedence. This object is the 64-bit version of cipPrecedenceSwitchedPkts.

cipPrecedenceHCSwitchedBytes.name: cipPrecedenceHCSwitchedBytes
cipPrecedenceHCSwitchedBytes.description: Traffic, in bytes, at the cipPrecedenceIpPrecedence precedence. This object is the 64-bit version of cipPrecedenceSwitchedBytes.

cipMacXTable.name: cipMacXTable
cipMacXTable.description: This table contains additional objects for the cipMacTable.

cipMacXEntry.name: cipMacXEntry
cipMacXEntry.description: An entry containing additional management information applicable to a particular MAC address.

cipMacHCSwitchedPkts.name: cipMacHCSwitchedPkts
cipMacHCSwitchedPkts.description: The high capacity counter in packets with respect to cipMacAddress. This object is the 64-bit version of cipMacSwitchedPkts.

cipMacHCSwitchedBytes.name: cipMacHCSwitchedBytes
cipMacHCSwitchedBytes.description: The counter in bytes with respect to cipMacAddress. This object is the 64-bit version of cipMacSwitchedBytes.

ciscoIpStatMIBCompliance.name: ciscoIpStatMIBCompliance
ciscoIpStatMIBCompliance.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the IP Statistics on a Cisco router.

ciscoIpStatMIBComplianceRev2.name: ciscoIpStatMIBComplianceRev2
ciscoIpStatMIBComplianceRev2.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the IP Statistics on a Cisco router. This deprecates ciscoIpStatMIBCompliance to provide 64-bit versions of packet and byte counter objects.

ciscoIpStatMIBGroup.name: ciscoIpStatMIBGroup
ciscoIpStatMIBGroup.description: A collection of objects providing IP Statistics monitoring. For interfaces that operate at speeds greater than 20,000,000 bits/second, it is recommended that the HC counters in the optional compliance section be supported and used.

ciscoIpStatHCMIBGroup.name: ciscoIpStatHCMIBGroup
ciscoIpStatHCMIBGroup.description: A collection of objects providing IP Statistics monitoring. This is recommended for high speed (high speed interfaces transmit and receive at speeds over 20,000,000 bits/second) network interfaces.
